<TITLE> New WB country head takes office Tuesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 9 (bdnews24.com)--Newly appointed World Bank country director Ellen Goldstein will join the Dhaka office on Tuesday. Goldstein, who replaced Xian Zhu, will direct the development of the World Bank's strategy to support Bangladesh, in association with country priorities and in the context of the changing global circumstances, the Bank said in a statement on Monday. She will also focus on further strengthening the capacity to manage public resources. Goldstein joined the World Bank in 1988 as a macroeconomist, and served as a senior economist for Bangladesh between 1990 and 1993, the statement said. For the past 13 years, she has held managerial positions of increasing responsibility, including her most recent assignment as country manager for Burkina Faso. For the past two years, Goldstein was on special assignment to the African Development Bank in Tunisia where she served most recently as director of Quality Assurance and Results. Prior to that, she was country director for programmes in nine West African nations. The World Bank had provided a record high in concessional IDA lending of US$1.1 billion to Bangladesh in the 2009 financial year. Currently, the Bank has 27 active operations in Bangladesh, of which seven were approved by the World Bank Board in fiscal year 2009, the statement said. bd
